<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="537" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herbert</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-11-02"><hi rend="italic">November 2,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my note of the 3d of
                            October last, I have the honor to inclose the copy of the note from the
                            Marquis of Salisbury to Count Hatzfeldt, of the 12th of August, which
                            should have accompanied my note of the 26th August last, in regard to
                            the difference of opinion <pb facs="0587" n="581" xml:id="pg_581"/>
                            which has arisen as to the apportionment of the import and export duties
                            in Samoa.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to renew at the same time the expression of my regret
                            that the wrong inclosure should have been sent you with my note of the
                            26th August.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Michael H.
                            Herbert.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>